The paper deals with the design and analysis of coded modulation schemes for optical communication systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of bit-wise decoders, which are commonly used in digital signal processing and optimization (cs.OH) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of low-density parity check codes, which are commonly used in networked information systems (cs.NI).
